value.value: The row of setae that is on the distal margin of the proximolateral galeal sclerite.
The lobe that is located medially on the internal wall of the galeo-lacinial complex and margined by the galeal comb.
The carina that extends medially along the medial wall of the galeo-lacinial complex and that is longitudinal.
The area on the lacinial lobe that is covered with acanthae.
The area on the galeo-lacinial complex distal to the lacinial lobe that is covered with acanthae.
The flange that is transparent, and extends along the anterodistal margin of the galeo-lacinial complex distal to the lacinial lobe.
The coeloconic sensillum that is located on the medial surface of the galeo-lacinial complex distal to the base of the lacinial lobe.
The sclerite that is located on the medial surface of the galeo-lacinial complex and bears the coeloconic sensillum of galea.
The sclerite that receives the site of insertion of the stipito-galeal muscle.
The area that is limited distally by the posterior margin of the prementum and laterally by the median margins of the cardines and the stipites.
The area that is located between the cardines and limited proximally and distally by the anatomical line that extends between the proximal and distal ends of the left and right cardines.

The area of the postmental area that is limited laterally by the median margins of the stipites, proximally by the anterior margin of the intercardinal area and distally by the proximal margin of the prementum.
The region that corresponds to the distal margin of the intercardinal area.
The sclerite on the intercardinal area that is not paired.
The intercardinal sclerite that is connected distally to the prearticular portion of the postmentum.
The interstipital sclerite that is connected proximally to the postarticular portion of the postmentum.
The articular process that bears the postmental articular surface of the prementum.
The area of the prementum, that lays parallel and connected via conjunctiva to the medial stipital vall.
The notch that is located distolaterally on the prementum and receives the base of the labial palp.
The area of the prementum that is located between the labial palpal excisions and is limited posteriorly by the anatomical line extending between the proximalmost points of the excisions.
The area of the lateral premental face that receives the site of origin of the dorsal premento-salivarial muscle.
The area of the prementum that is delimited laterally by the lateral premental face.
The flange that is adjacent to the border between the ventral and lateral premental faces and that overlaps externally the median part of the posterior stipital sclerite.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the sclerites that articulate with the ninth abdominal tergite and the second valvifer.

label.value: posterior margin of the first valvifer

value.value: The margin of the first valvifer that is posterior and extends between the intervalvifer articulation and the anterior angle of the first valvifer.

label.value: ninth tergal condyle of the first valvifer

value.value: The condyle that is located on the first valvifer and articulates with the first valviferal fossa of T9.

label.value: first valviferal fossa of the ninth tergite

value.value: The fossa of the ninth abdominal tergite that is adjacent to the condyle of the ninth tergal condyle of the first valvifer.
The conjunctiva that traverses the first valvifer and separates the dorsal and ventral sclerites of the first valvifer.

label.value: dorsal sclerite of the first valvifer

value.value: The sclerite of the first valvifer that is located dorsally of the transvalviferal conjunctiva.

label.value: ventral sclerite of the first valvifer

value.value: The sclerite of the first valvifer that is ventral to the transvalviferal conjunctiva.
The articulation between the dorsal sclerite of the first valvifer and the ventral sclerite of the first valvifer.

label.value: anterior flange of the first valvifer

value.value: The flange that extends anteriorly on the first valvifer and overlaps with the posterior margin of the anterior area of the second valvifer.

label.value: second valviferal condyle of the first valvifer

value.value: The condyle that is located on the first valvifer and articulates with the first valviferal fossa of the second valvifer.

label.value: anterior area of the second valvifer

value.value: The area of the second valvifer which is anterior to the anatomical line that is the shortest distance from the first valviferal fossa of the second valvifer and the ventral margin of the second valvifer.

label.value: posterior area of the second valvifer

value.value: the area of the second valvifer that is posterior to the anatomical line that is the shortest distance from the first valviferal fossa of the second valvifer to the ventral margin of the second valvifer

label.value: basal line of the second valvifer

value.value: The line on the second valvifer that extends between the pars articularis and the dorsal flange of second valvifer.

label.value: dorsal projection of the second valvifer

value.value: The projection that is located on the second valvifer and corresponds to the proximal end of the rachis.

label.value: anterior section of dorsal flange of second valvifer

value.value: The area of the anterior area of the second valvifer that is anterior to the site of origin of the basal line, continuous with the dorsal flange of the second valvifer and marks the site of origin of the dorsal T9-2nd valvifer muscle part b.

label.value: posterior section of dorsal flange of second valvifer

value.value: The area of the dorsal flange of the second valvifer that is posterior to the to the site of origin of the basal line.
The area that is connected to the ninth tergite and the first valvifer via conjunctiva, is articulated to the first tergite, and bears the aulax.
The anterior area of the dorsal valve that is bulbous.

label.value: anterior notch of the dorsal valve

value.value: The notch that is on the anterior region of the dorsal valve and accommodates the ventral ramus of the second valvula and the first valvula.

label.value: distal notch of the dorsal valve

value.value: The notch that is distal on the dorsal valve.

label.value: distal vertical conjunctiva of the second valvifer-third valvula complex

value.value: The conjunctiva that traverses the second valvifer-third valvula complex and is located distal to the median bridge of the second valvifer.
The area of the second valvifer-second valvula-third valvula complex that is proximal to the basal articulation.
The ridge that extends along the anterior margin of female T9 and receives the site of origin of the ventral and the dorsal T9-second valvifer muscles.
The sclerite that is part of the maxillary palp.
The area of muscle attachment.
The sternite that is connected to the first valvula via muscles.
The muscle that arises from the posteroventral parts of the female T9 and inserts on the median bridge.
